title: Are Fetal Cells Used to Make Vaccines?
description: Paul A. Offit, MD, discusses the use of fetal cells to make vaccines, highlighting how and why fetal cells are involved in the vaccine development process and the Catholic Church’s interpretation of the use of these vaccines. For more information and resources about the use of fetal cells in vaccines, visit: http://www.chop.edu/centers-programs/vaccine-education-center/vaccine-ingredients/fetal-tissues
